text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described in 1881 by Ferdinand von Mueller and the description was published in Fragmenta phytographiae Australiae. The specific epithet (fraseri) honours Sir Malcolm Fraser, the Surveyor-General of Western Australia from 1872 to 1883.There are two subspecies:

Eremophila fraseri  F.Muell.  subsp. fraseri which has egg-shaped leaves that are mostly wider than 14 millimetres (0.6 in);
Eremophila fraseri subsp. parva  Chinnock  which has oblong to elliptic leaves that are mostly narrower than 12 millimetres (0.5 in).
